(UNHEX('00112233445566778899AABBCCDDEEFF'), 'Delicious Pancakes', '2023-01-01', 5, 'Fluffy and easy to make.', 'Breakfast', UNHEX('AABBCCDDEEFF00112233445566778899'), '# Delicious Pancakes\n\n## Introduction\nFluffy and easy-to-make pancakes that are perfect for breakfast. Serve them with syrup, fruits, or your favorite toppings.\n\n## Ingredients\n- 1 cup all-purpose flour\n- 2 tablespoons sugar\n- 1 tablespoon baking powder\n- 1/2 teaspoon salt\n- 1 cup milk\n- 1 egg\n- 2 tablespoons melted butter\n- 1 teaspoon vanilla extract\n\n## Instructions\n1. **Mix dry ingredients**: In a large bowl, whisk together flour, sugar, baking powder, and salt.\n2. **Add wet ingredients**: In another bowl, mix milk, egg, melted butter, and vanilla extract.\n3. **Combine**: Pour the wet ingredients into the dry ingredients and mix until just combined. Do not overmix.\n4. **Cook**: Heat a non-stick skillet over medium heat. Pour 1/4 cup of batter for each pancake. Cook until bubbles form on the surface, then flip and cook until golden brown.\n5. **Serve**: Serve warm with your favorite toppings.\n\n## Tips\n- Do not overmix the batter; lumps are okay.\n- For extra fluffiness, let the batter rest for a few minutes before cooking.\n- Add blueberries or chocolate chips to the batter for a fun twist.'),
(UNHEX('00112233445566778899AABBCCDDEE00'), 'Quick Spaghetti', '2023-01-02', 4, 'A quick and easy spaghetti recipe.', 'Pasta', UNHEX('AABBCCDDEEFF00112233445566778899'), '# Quick Spaghetti\n\n## Introduction\nThis quick spaghetti recipe is perfect for busy weeknights. It’s simple, tasty, and ready in just 20 minutes.\n\n## Ingredients\n- 8 oz spaghetti\n- 2 tablespoons olive oil\n- 3 cloves garlic, minced\n- 1/4 teaspoon red pepper flakes\n- 1 can (14.5 oz) diced tomatoes\n- 1/2 teaspoon salt\n- 1/4 teaspoon black pepper\n- 1/4 cup grated Parmesan cheese\n- Fresh basil for garnish\n\n## Instructions\n1. **Cook spaghetti**: Cook spaghetti according to package instructions. Drain and set aside.\n2. **Prepare sauce**: In a large skillet, heat olive oil over medium heat. Add garlic and red pepper flakes, and cook for 1 minute.\n3. **Add tomatoes**: Add diced tomatoes, salt, and pepper. Cook for 5-7 minutes, until the sauce thickens slightly.\n4. **Combine**: Add cooked spaghetti to the skillet and toss to coat with the sauce.\n5. **Serve**: Serve topped with grated Parmesan cheese and fresh basil.\n\n## Tips\n- Use high-quality canned tomatoes for the best flavor.\n- Add cooked chicken or shrimp for extra protein.\n- For a spicier kick, increase the amount of red pepper flakes.'),
(UNHEX('00112233445566778899AABBCCDDEE01'), 'Classic Margherita Pizza', '2023-01-03', 5, 'A classic Italian pizza with fresh mozzarella and basil.', 'Italian', UNHEX('AABBCCDDEEFF00112233445566778899'), '# Classic Margherita Pizza\n\n## Introduction\nThis Classic Margherita Pizza is a celebration of simple, fresh ingredients. With a crisp crust, fresh mozzarella, and aromatic basil, it’s a pizza that’s perfect for any time of year.\n\n## Ingredients\n- 1 pizza dough\n- 1 cup tomato sauce\n- 2 cups fresh mozzarella, sliced\n- Fresh basil leaves\n- 1 tbsp olive oil\n- Salt to taste\n\n## Instructions\n1. **Preheat oven**: Preheat your oven to 475°F (245°C).\n2. **Prepare dough**: Roll out the pizza dough on a floured surface to your desired thickness.\n3. **Add sauce**: Spread the tomato sauce evenly over the dough.\n4. **Add cheese**: Place the sliced mozzarella evenly over the sauce.\n5. **Bake**: Bake in the preheated oven for 10-12 minutes, or until the crust is golden and the cheese is bubbly.\n6. **Add basil**: Remove from the oven and scatter fresh basil leaves over the top. Drizzle with olive oil and sprinkle with salt.\n\n## Tips\n- For a crispier crust, bake the pizza on a preheated pizza stone.\n- Use high-quality mozzarella and fresh basil for the best flavor.\n- If you don’t have fresh basil, you can use dried basil but add it before baking.'),
(UNHEX('00112233445566778899AABBCCDDEE02'), 'Spaghetti Carbonara', '2023-01-04', 4, 'Creamy and delicious Italian pasta.', 'Pasta', UNHEX('AABBCCDDEEFF00112233445566778899'), '# Spaghetti Carbonara\n\n## Introduction\nSpaghetti Carbonara is a rich and creamy pasta dish that’s both simple and indulgent. With a blend of eggs, cheese, pancetta, and pepper, it’s a quick meal that feels luxurious.\n\n## Ingredients\n- 1 pound spaghetti\n- 2 large eggs\n- 1 cup grated Parmesan cheese\n- 4 slices pancetta, diced\n- 4 cloves garlic, minced\n- Salt and black pepper to taste\n\n## Instructions\n1. **Cook pasta**: Cook spaghetti according to package instructions. Reserve 1 cup of pasta water and drain the rest.\n2. **Cook pancetta**: In a large pan, cook pancetta over medium heat until crispy. Add garlic and cook for another minute.\n3. **Mix eggs and cheese**: In a bowl, whisk together eggs and Parmesan cheese.\n4. **Combine**: Add hot pasta to the pan with pancetta and garlic. Remove from heat and quickly mix in the egg and cheese mixture, adding reserved pasta water a little at a time to create a creamy sauce.\n5. **Season**: Season with salt and plenty of black pepper. Serve immediately.\n\n## Tips\n- Work quickly when mixing the egg and cheese mixture to avoid scrambling the eggs.\n- Use freshly grated Parmesan for the best flavor and texture.\n- If pancetta is not available, substitute with bacon or guanciale.'),
(UNHEX('00112233445566778899AABBCCDDEE03'), 'Fresh Summer Salad', '2023-01-05', 3, 'Light and refreshing salad perfect for summer.', 'Salad', UNHEX('AABBCCDDEEFF00112233445566778899'), '# Fresh Summer Salad\n\n## Introduction\nThis Fresh Summer Salad is a vibrant mix of seasonal vegetables and a light vinaigrette. It’s the perfect side dish for any summer meal, offering a refreshing crunch and burst of flavor.\n\n## Ingredients\n- 2 cups mixed greens\n- 1 cup cherry tomatoes, halved\n- 1 cucumber, sliced\n- 1 red bell pepper, sliced\n- 1/2 red onion, thinly sliced\n- 1 avocado, diced\n- 1/4 cup feta cheese, crumbled\n- 1/4 cup olive oil\n- 2 tbsp balsamic vinegar\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n\n## Instructions\n1. **Prepare vegetables**: Wash and cut all vegetables as instructed.\n2. **Combine ingredients**: In a large bowl, combine mixed greens, cherry tomatoes, cucumber, red bell pepper, red onion, and avocado.\n3. **Add cheese**: Sprinkle feta cheese over the salad.\n4. **Make dressing**: In a small bowl, whisk together olive oil, balsamic vinegar, salt, and pepper.\n5. **Toss salad**: Drizzle dressing over the salad and toss gently to combine. Serve immediately.\n\n## Tips\n- Use fresh, seasonal vegetables for the best flavor and nutrition.\n- Add grilled chicken or shrimp for a heartier meal.\n- If you’re preparing the salad in advance, keep the dressing separate until ready to serve.'),
(UNHEX('00112233445566778899AABBCCDDEE04'), 'Hearty Beef Stew', '2023-01-06', 4, 'A comforting and filling beef stew.', 'Dinner', UNHEX('AABBCCDDEEFF00112233445566778899'), '# Hearty Beef Stew\n\n## Introduction\nThis hearty beef stew is a perfect comfort food, especially on cold days. It’s packed with tender beef, vegetables, and rich, savory broth.\n\n## Ingredients\n- 2 pounds beef stew meat, cubed\n- 3 tablespoons flour\n- 2 tablespoons olive oil\n- 1 large onion, chopped\n- 3 cloves garlic, minced\n- 4 cups beef broth\n- 2 cups water\n- 1 cup red wine (optional)\n- 4 carrots, sliced\n- 3 potatoes, diced\n- 2 stalks celery, sliced\n- 1 teaspoon dried thyme\n- 1 teaspoon salt\n- 1/2 teaspoon black pepper\n\n## Instructions\n1. **Prepare beef**: Toss beef cubes in flour until evenly coated.\n2. **Brown beef**: Heat olive oil in a large pot over medium-high heat. Add beef and brown on all sides. Remove and set aside.\n3. **Cook vegetables**: In the same pot, add onion and garlic. Cook until softened.\n4. **Add liquids**: Return beef to the pot. Add beef broth, water, and wine. Bring to a boil.\n5. **Simmer**: Reduce heat to low. Add carrots, potatoes, celery, thyme, salt, and pepper. Cover and simmer for 1.5 to 2 hours until beef is tender.\n6. **Serve**: Serve hot with crusty bread or over mashed potatoes.\n\n## Tips\n- For extra depth of flavor, deglaze the pot with a bit of the red wine before adding the liquids.\n- Use a slow cooker for convenience: follow steps 1-3, then transfer everything to a slow cooker and cook on low for 6-8 hours.\n- Adjust seasoning to taste before serving.'),
(UNHEX('00112233445566778899AABBCCDDEE05'), 'Grilled Cheese Sandwich', '2023-01-07', 5, 'A classic grilled cheese sandwich.', 'Lunch', UNHEX('AABBCCDDEEFF00112233445566778899'), '# Grilled Cheese Sandwich\n\n## Introduction\nA classic grilled cheese sandwich that’s crispy on the outside and gooey on the inside. Perfect for a quick and satisfying lunch.\n\n## Ingredients\n- 2 slices of bread\n- 2 tablespoons butter, softened\n- 2 slices of cheddar cheese\n\n## Instructions\n1. **Butter bread**: Spread butter evenly on one side of each slice of bread.\n2. **Assemble sandwich**: Place one slice of bread, buttered side down, in a skillet. Add cheese slices and top with the second slice of bread, buttered side up.\n3. **Cook**: Heat skillet over medium heat. Cook the sandwich until the bread is golden brown and the cheese is melted, about 2-3 minutes per side.\n4. **Serve**: Slice in half and serve warm.\n\n## Tips\n- Use a mix of cheeses for added flavor.\n- Add tomato slices or cooked bacon for variation.\n- Cook on low heat if the bread browns too quickly before the cheese melts.'),
(UNHEX('00112233445566778899AABBCCDDEE06'), 'Mango Smoothie', '2023-01-08', 4, 'A refreshing mango smoothie.', 'Beverage', UNHEX('AABBCCDDEEFF00112233445566778899'), '# Mango Smoothie\n\n## Introduction\nA refreshing and creamy mango smoothie that’s perfect for a hot day or a quick breakfast on the go.\n\n## Ingredients\n- 1 cup frozen mango chunks\n- 1/2 cup Greek yogurt\n- 1/2 cup milk or almond milk\n- 1 tablespoon honey\n- 1/2 teaspoon vanilla extract\n\n## Instructions\n1. **Blend ingredients**: Combine all ingredients in a blender.\n2. **Blend until smooth**: Blend on high speed until smooth and creamy.\n3. **Serve**: Pour into a glass and enjoy immediately.\n\n## Tips\n- Add a handful of spinach for extra nutrients.\n- Substitute the Greek yogurt with a plant-based yogurt for a vegan option.\n- Adjust the sweetness by adding more or less honey.'),
(UNHEX('00112233445566778899AABBCCDDEE07'), 'Veggie Stir Fry', '2023-01-09', 5, 'A quick and easy veggie stir fry.', 'Vegetarian', UNHEX('AABBCCDDEEFF00112233445566778899'), '# Veggie Stir Fry\n\n## Introduction\nThis veggie stir fry is a quick and healthy meal, packed with colorful vegetables and a flavorful sauce. Perfect for a busy weeknight dinner.\n\n## Ingredients\n- 1 tablespoon vegetable oil\n- 2 cloves garlic, minced\n- 1 bell pepper, sliced\n- 1 cup broccoli florets\n- 1 carrot, sliced\n- 1 zucchini, sliced\n- 2 tablespoons soy sauce\n- 1 tablespoon hoisin sauce\n- 1 teaspoon sesame oil\n- 1/4 cup water\n- Cooked rice for serving\n\n## Instructions\n1. **Heat oil**: Heat vegetable oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat.\n2. **Cook garlic**: Add garlic and cook for 30 seconds until fragrant.\n3. **Add vegetables**: Add bell pepper, broccoli, carrot, and zucchini. Stir fry for 5-7 minutes until vegetables are tender-crisp.\n4. **Add sauce**: In a small bowl, mix soy sauce, hoisin sauce, sesame oil, and water. Pour over vegetables and stir to coat evenly.\n5. **Serve**: Serve hot over cooked rice.\n\n## Tips\n- Add your favorite protein like tofu, chicken, or shrimp.\n- Adjust the sauce ingredients to taste.\n- Garnish with sesame seeds and green onions for extra flavor.'),
(UNHEX('00112233445566778899AABBCCDDEE08'), 'Chicken Alfredo', '2023-01-10', 5, 'Creamy and delicious chicken alfredo pasta.', 'Dinner', UNHEX('AABBCCDDEEFF00112233445566778899'), '# Chicken Alfredo\n\n## Introduction\nA creamy and delicious chicken Alfredo pasta that’s easy to make and perfect for a comforting dinner.\n\n## Ingredients\n- 2 tablespoons butter\n- 2 cloves garlic, minced\n- 1 cup heavy cream\n- 1 cup grated Parmesan cheese\n- 1 pound cooked chicken breast, sliced\n- 8 oz fettuccine pasta, cooked\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n- Fresh parsley for garnish\n\n## Instructions\n1. **Melt butter**: In a large skillet, melt butter over medium heat.\n2. **Cook garlic**: Add garlic and cook for 1 minute until fragrant.\n3. **Add cream**: Stir in heavy cream and bring to a simmer.\n4. **Add cheese**: Stir in Parmesan cheese until melted and the sauce is smooth.\n5. **Combine**: Add cooked chicken and pasta to the skillet. Toss to coat with the sauce. Season with salt and pepper.\n6. **Serve**: Serve garnished with fresh parsley.\n\n## Tips\n- Use freshly grated Parmesan for the best flavor and texture.\n- Add a pinch of nutmeg to the sauce for extra depth of flavor.\n- For a lighter version, substitute heavy cream with half-and-half.'),
(UNHEX('00112233445566778899AABBCCDDEE09'), 'Taco Salad', '2023-01-11', 4, 'A fresh and tasty taco salad.', 'Salad', UNHEX('AABBCCDDEEFF00112233445566778899'), '# Taco Salad\n\n## Introduction\nA fresh and tasty taco salad that’s perfect for a light lunch or dinner. Packed with all your favorite taco flavors and a delicious homemade dressing.\n\n## Ingredients\n- 1 pound ground beef\n- 1 packet taco seasoning mix\n- 1 head romaine lettuce, chopped\n- 1 cup cherry tomatoes, halved\n- 1/2 cup black beans, rinsed and drained\n- 1/2 cup corn kernels\n- 1/4 cup red onion, diced\n- 1 avocado, diced\n- 1/2 cup shredded cheddar cheese\n- 1/4 cup sour cream\n- 1/4 cup salsa\n\n## Instructions\n1. **Cook beef**: In a large skillet, cook ground beef over medium heat until browned. Drain excess fat. Stir in taco seasoning mix and water according to package instructions.\n2. **Prepare vegetables**: In a large bowl, combine lettuce, tomatoes, black beans, corn, red onion, and avocado.\n3. **Assemble salad**: Add cooked beef to the bowl. Sprinkle with shredded cheese.\n4. **Make dressing**: In a small bowl, mix sour cream and salsa.\n5. **Serve**: Drizzle dressing over the salad and toss to combine.\n\n## Tips\n- Use ground turkey or chicken for a leaner option.\n- Add crushed tortilla chips for extra crunch.\n- Serve with lime wedges for a fresh burst of flavor.'),
(UNHEX('00112233445566778899AABBCCDDEE0A'), 'Blueberry Muffins', '2023-01-12', 4, 'Sweet and delicious blueberry muffins.', 'Breakfast', UNHEX('AABBCCDDEEFF00112233445566778899'), '# Blueberry Muffins\n\n## Introduction\nSweet and delicious blueberry muffins that are perfect for breakfast or a snack. These muffins are packed with juicy blueberries and have a tender crumb.\n\n## Ingredients\n- 1 1/2 cups all-purpose flour\n- 3/4 cup sugar\n- 1/2 teaspoon salt\n- 2 teaspoons baking powder\n- 1/3 cup vegetable oil\n- 1 egg\n- 1/3 cup milk\n- 1 cup fresh blueberries\n\n## Instructions\n1. **Preheat oven**: Preheat your oven to 400°F (200°C). Grease a muffin tin or line with paper muffin cups.\n2. **Mix dry ingredients**: In a large bowl, mix together flour, sugar, salt, and baking powder.\n3. **Add wet ingredients**: In another bowl, beat together vegetable oil, egg, and milk. Stir into the flour mixture until just combined. Fold in blueberries.\n4. **Fill muffin cups**: Fill the muffin cups about 2/3 full with batter.\n5. **Bake**: Bake for 20-25 minutes, until a toothpick inserted into the center of a muffin comes out clean.\n6. **Cool**: Let muffins cool in the pan for 10 minutes, then transfer to a wire rack to cool completely.\n\n## Tips\n- Use fresh or frozen blueberries; if using frozen, do not thaw.\n- Add a streusel topping for extra crunch and sweetness.\n- Store muffins in an airtight container for up to 3 days.'),
(UNHEX('00112233445566778899AABBCCDDEE0B'), 'Chocolate Brownies', '2023-01-13', 5, 'Rich and fudgy chocolate brownies.', 'Dessert', UNHEX('AABBCCDDEEFF00112233445566778899'), '# Chocolate Brownies\n\n## Introduction\nRich and fudgy chocolate brownies that are perfect for any chocolate lover. These brownies have a dense and chewy texture with a crackly top.\n\n## Ingredients\n- 1/2 cup butter, melted\n- 1 cup sugar\n- 2 eggs\n- 1 teaspoon vanilla extract\n- 1/3 cup cocoa powder\n- 1/2 cup all-purpose flour\n- 1/4 teaspoon salt\n- 1/4 teaspoon baking powder\n\n## Instructions\n1. **Preheat oven**: Preheat your oven to 350°F (175°C). Grease and flour an 8x8 inch baking pan.\n2. **Mix wet ingredients**: In a large bowl, mix melted butter, sugar, eggs, and vanilla extract.\n3. **Add dry ingredients**: Add cocoa powder, flour, salt, and baking powder. Mix until just combined.\n4. **Bake**: Pour batter into the prepared pan and bake for 20-25 minutes, until a toothpick inserted into the center comes out clean.\n5. **Cool**: Let brownies cool in the pan before cutting into squares.\n\n## Tips\n- For extra fudgy brownies, reduce the baking time slightly.\n- Add chocolate chips or nuts to the batter for added texture and flavor.\n- Serve with a scoop of ice cream for an indulgent treat.'),
(UNHEX('00112233445566778899AABBCCDDEE0C'), 'Caesar Salad', '2023-01-14', 5, 'A classic Caesar salad.', 'Salad', UNHEX('AABBCCDDEEFF00112233445566778899'), '# Caesar Salad\n\n## Introduction\nA classic Caesar salad with crisp romaine lettuce, creamy Caesar dressing, crunchy croutons, and Parmesan cheese. Perfect as a side dish or a light meal.\n\n## Ingredients\n- 1 head romaine lettuce, chopped\n- 1/4 cup grated Parmesan cheese\n- 1 cup croutons\n- 1/4 cup Caesar dressing\n\n## Instructions\n1. **Prepare lettuce**: Wash and chop the romaine lettuce. Place in a large salad bowl.\n2. **Add toppings**: Add grated Parmesan cheese and croutons to the lettuce.\n3. **Dress salad**: Drizzle Caesar dressing over the salad and toss to combine.\n4. **Serve**: Serve immediately, topped with extra Parmesan cheese if desired.\n\n## Tips\n- Use homemade croutons for added flavor and crunch.\n- Add grilled chicken or shrimp for a heartier meal.\n- Make your own Caesar dressing for a fresher taste.'),
(UNHEX('00112233445566778899AABBCCDDEE0D'), 'Tomato Soup', '2023-01-15', 4, 'A warm and comforting tomato soup.', 'Soup', UNHEX('AABBCCDDEEFF00112233445566778899'), '# Tomato Soup\n\n## Introduction\nA warm and comforting tomato soup that’s perfect for a chilly day. This soup is easy to make and full of rich tomato flavor.\n\n## Ingredients\n- 2 tablespoons olive oil\n- 1 onion, chopped\n- 2 cloves garlic, minced\n- 4 cups canned crushed tomatoes\n- 2 cups chicken broth\n- 1 teaspoon sugar\n- 1/2 teaspoon salt\n- 1/4 teaspoon black pepper\n- 1/2 cup heavy cream\n- Fresh basil for garnish\n\n## Instructions\n1. **Cook onions**: In a large pot, heat olive oil over medium heat. Add onion and cook until soft.\n2. **Add garlic**: Add garlic and cook for another minute.\n3. **Add tomatoes and broth**: Stir in crushed tomatoes and chicken broth. Bring to a simmer.\n4. **Season**: Add sugar, salt, and black pepper. Simmer for 15-20 minutes.\n5. **Blend soup**: Use an immersion blender to puree the soup until smooth. Stir in heavy cream.\n6. **Serve**: Serve hot, garnished with fresh basil.\n\n## Tips\n- For a thicker soup, add a tablespoon of tomato paste.\n- Serve with grilled cheese sandwiches for a classic combination.\n- Add a pinch of red pepper flakes for a spicy kick.'),
(UNHEX('00112233445566778899AABBCCDDEE0E'), 'Garlic Bread', '2023-01-16', 5, 'Crispy and flavorful garlic bread.', 'Side', UNHEX('AABBCCDDEEFF00112233445566778899'), '# Garlic Bread\n\n## Introduction\nCrispy and flavorful garlic bread that’s perfect as a side dish for pasta or soups. This easy recipe uses simple ingredients and comes together quickly.\n\n## Ingredients\n- 1 loaf French bread, sliced in half lengthwise\n- 1/2 cup butter, softened\n- 4 cloves garlic, minced\n- 2 tablespoons fresh parsley, chopped\n- 1/4 cup grated Parmesan cheese\n\n## Instructions\n1. **Preheat oven**: Preheat your oven to 350°F (175°C).\n2. **Prepare butter mixture**: In a bowl, mix butter, garlic, parsley, and Parmesan cheese.\n3. **Spread on bread**: Spread the butter mixture evenly over the cut sides of the bread.\n4. **Bake**: Place the bread on a baking sheet and bake for 10-15 minutes, until the bread is crispy and the butter is melted.\n5. **Serve**: Cut into slices and serve warm.\n\n## Tips\n- Use a combination of fresh and dried herbs for added flavor.\n- Add a sprinkle of mozzarella cheese for a cheesy garlic bread.\n- Serve with marinara sauce for dipping.'),
(UNHEX('00112233445566778899AABBCCDDEE0F'), 'Quinoa Salad', '2023-01-17', 3, 'A healthy and nutritious quinoa salad.', 'Salad', UNHEX('AABBCCDDEEFF00112233445566778899'), '# Quinoa Salad\n\n## Introduction\nA healthy and nutritious quinoa salad that’s perfect as a light lunch or a side dish. This salad is packed with fresh vegetables and a tangy dressing.\n\n## Ingredients\n- 1 cup quinoa\n- 2 cups water\n- 1 cup cherry tomatoes, halved\n- 1 cucumber, diced\n- 1 bell pepper, diced\n- 1/4 cup red onion, diced\n- 1/4 cup fresh parsley, chopped\n- 1/4 cup feta cheese, crumbled\n- 1/4 cup olive oil\n- 2 tablespoons lemon juice\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n\n## Instructions\n1. **Cook quinoa**: In a saucepan, bring quinoa and water to a boil. Reduce heat to low, cover, and simmer for 15 minutes or until water is absorbed. Let cool.\n2. **Prepare vegetables**: While the quinoa is cooking, chop the cherry tomatoes, cucumber, bell pepper, and red onion. \n3. **Combine ingredients**: In a large bowl, combine the cooked quinoa, cherry tomatoes, cucumber, bell pepper, red onion, fresh parsley, and feta cheese.\n4. **Make dressing**: In a small bowl, whisk together olive oil, lemon juice, salt, and pepper.\n5. **Toss salad**: Pour the dressing over the salad and toss to combine. Serve immediately.\n\n## Tips\n- For added protein, you can add chickpeas or grilled chicken to the salad.\n- Make sure to let the quinoa cool before mixing it with the vegetables to prevent wilting.\n- Store any leftovers in an airtight container in the refrigerator for up to 3 days.'),
(UNHEX('00112233445566778899AABBCCDDEE10'), 'Banana Bread', '2023-01-18', 5, 'Moist and flavorful banana bread.', 'Dessert', UNHEX('AABBCCDDEEFF00112233445566778899'), '# Banana Bread\n\n## Introduction\nMoist and flavorful banana bread that’s perfect for breakfast or a snack. Made with ripe bananas, this bread is a great way to use up overripe bananas.\n\n## Ingredients\n- 2 to 3 ripe bananas, mashed\n- 1/3 cup melted butter\n- 1 teaspoon baking soda\n- Pinch of salt\n- 3/4 cup sugar\n- 1 large egg, beaten\n- 1 teaspoon vanilla extract\n- 1 1/2 cups all-purpose flour\n\n## Instructions\n1. **Preheat oven**: Preheat your oven to 350°F (175°C). Grease a 9x5 inch loaf pan.\n2. **Mix ingredients**: In a mixing bowl, mash the ripe bananas with a fork until smooth. Stir in the melted butter. Mix in the baking soda and salt. Stir in the sugar, beaten egg, and vanilla extract. Mix in the flour.\n3. **Bake**: Pour the batter into the prepared loaf pan. Bake for 60-65 minutes, or until a tester inserted into the center comes out clean.\n4. **Cool**: Let the banana bread cool in the pan for 10 minutes, then transfer to a wire rack to cool completely.\n\n## Tips\n- Add nuts or chocolate chips to the batter for extra flavor and texture.\n- Use very ripe bananas for the best flavor and sweetness.\n- Store banana bread in an airtight container to keep it moist.'),
(UNHEX('00112233445566778899AABBCCDDEE11'), 'Chicken Tacos', '2023-01-19', 4, 'Spicy and delicious chicken tacos.', 'Mexican', UNHEX('AABBCCDDEEFF00112233445566778899'), '# Chicken Tacos\n\n## Introduction\nSpicy and delicious chicken tacos that are perfect for a quick and tasty dinner. These tacos are packed with flavor and easy to make.\n\n## Ingredients\n- 1 pound boneless, skinless chicken breasts, cut into strips\n- 1 tablespoon olive oil\n- 1 packet taco seasoning mix\n- 1/2 cup water\n- 8 small flour or corn tortillas\n- 1 cup shredded lettuce\n- 1/2 cup diced tomatoes\n- 1/2 cup shredded cheddar cheese\n- 1/4 cup sour cream\n- 1/4 cup salsa\n\n## Instructions\n1. **Cook chicken**: In a large skillet, heat olive oil over medium-high heat. Add chicken strips and cook until browned and cooked through.\n2. **Add seasoning**: Stir in taco seasoning mix and water. Cook for 2-3 minutes until the sauce thickens and the chicken is well coated.\n3. **Prepare tortillas**: Warm tortillas in a dry skillet or microwave until soft.\n4. **Assemble tacos**: Fill each tortilla with chicken, shredded lettuce, diced tomatoes, shredded cheese, sour cream, and salsa.\n5. **Serve**: Serve immediately with your favorite taco toppings.\n\n## Tips\n- Use rotisserie chicken for a quick and easy option.\n- Add avocado or guacamole for extra creaminess.\n- Serve with lime wedges for a fresh burst of flavor.'),
(UNHEX('00112233445566778899AABBCCDDEE12'), 'Pasta Primavera', '2023-01-20', 5, 'A light and fresh pasta primavera.', 'Pasta', UNHEX('AABBCCDDEEFF00112233445566778899'), '# Pasta Primavera\n\n## Introduction\nA light and fresh pasta primavera that’s perfect for spring and summer. This dish is full of colorful vegetables and a simple, flavorful sauce.\n\n## Ingredients\n- 12 oz pasta (penne, farfalle, or your favorite)\n- 2 tablespoons olive oil\n- 1 red bell pepper, sliced\n- 1 yellow bell pepper, sliced\n- 1 zucchini, sliced\n- 1 cup cherry tomatoes, halved\n- 3 cloves garlic, minced\n- 1/2 cup grated Parmesan cheese\n- 1/4 cup fresh basil, chopped\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n\n## Instructions\n1. **Cook pasta**: Cook pasta according to package instructions. Drain and set aside.\n2. **Heat oil**: In a large skillet, heat olive oil over medium heat.\n3. **Cook vegetables**: Add bell peppers, zucchini, and cherry tomatoes. Cook for 5-7 minutes until vegetables are tender.\n4. **Add garlic**: Add minced garlic and cook for another minute.\n5. **Combine**: Add cooked pasta to the skillet and toss to combine with the vegetables. Stir in grated Parmesan cheese and fresh basil. Season with salt and pepper.\n6. **Serve**: Serve hot, topped with extra Parmesan cheese if desired.\n\n## Tips\n- Add cooked chicken or shrimp for extra protein.\n- Use whole wheat pasta for a healthier option.\n- Serve with a side of garlic bread.'),
(UNHEX('00112233445566778899AABBCCDDEE13'), 'Fish Tacos', '2023-01-21', 5, 'Crispy and flavorful fish tacos.', 'Mexican', UNHEX('AABBCCDDEEFF00112233445566778899'), '# Fish Tacos\n\n## Introduction\nCrispy and flavorful fish tacos that are perfect for a light and refreshing meal. These tacos are easy to make and packed with flavor.\n\n## Ingredients\n- 1 pound white fish fillets (cod, tilapia, or your favorite)\n- 1 cup all-purpose flour\n- 2 eggs, beaten\n- 1 cup panko breadcrumbs\n- 1/2 teaspoon salt\n- 1/4 teaspoon black pepper\n- 8 small flour or corn tortillas\n- 1 cup shredded cabbage\n- 1/2 cup diced tomatoes\n- 1/4 cup sour cream\n- 1/4 cup salsa\n- 1 lime, cut into wedges\n\n## Instructions\n1. **Prepare fish**: Cut fish fillets into strips.\n2. **Bread fish**: Place flour, beaten eggs, and panko breadcrumbs in separate shallow bowls. Season flour with salt and pepper. Dredge each fish strip in flour, dip in eggs, and coat with breadcrumbs.\n3. **Cook fish**: Heat oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat. Fry fish strips until golden brown and cooked through, about 2-3 minutes per side.\n4. **Prepare tortillas**: Warm tortillas in a dry skillet or microwave until soft.\n5. **Assemble tacos**: Fill each tortilla with crispy fish, shredded cabbage, diced tomatoes, sour cream, and salsa. Serve with lime wedges.\n\n## Tips\n- Use a mix of red and green cabbage for extra color and crunch.\n- Add avocado or guacamole for extra creaminess.\n- Serve with lime wedges for a fresh burst of flavor.'),
(UNHEX('00112233445566778899AABBCCDDEE14'), 'Spinach Smoothie', '2023-01-22', 4, 'A healthy and refreshing spinach smoothie.', 'Beverage', UNHEX('AABBCCDDEEFF00112233445566778899'), '# Spinach Smoothie\n\n## Introduction\nA healthy and refreshing spinach smoothie that’s perfect for a quick breakfast or a post-workout snack. Packed with nutrients, it’s a great way to start your day.\n\n## Ingredients\n- 1 banana\n- 1 cup fresh spinach\n- 1/2 cup Greek yogurt\n- 1/2 cup milk or almond milk\n- 1 tablespoon honey\n- 1/2 teaspoon vanilla extract\n\n## Instructions\n1. **Blend ingredients**: Combine all ingredients in a blender.\n2. **Blend until smooth**: Blend on high speed until smooth and creamy.\n3. **Serve**: Pour into a glass and enjoy immediately.\n\n## Tips\n- Add a handful of frozen berries for extra flavor and nutrients.\n- Substitute Greek yogurt with a plant-based yogurt for a vegan option.\n- Adjust the sweetness by adding more or less honey.'),
(UNHEX('00112233445566778899AABBCCDDEE15'), 'Beef Tacos', '2023-01-23', 5, 'Juicy and flavorful beef tacos.', 'Mexican', UNHEX('AABBCCDDEEFF00112233445566778899'), '# Beef Tacos\n\n## Introduction\nJuicy and flavorful beef tacos that are perfect for a quick and tasty dinner. These tacos are packed with flavor and easy to make.\n\n## Ingredients\n- 1 pound ground beef\n- 1 packet taco seasoning mix\n- 1/2 cup water\n- 8 small flour or corn tortillas\n- 1 cup shredded lettuce\n- 1/2 cup diced tomatoes\n- 1/2 cup shredded cheddar cheese\n- 1/4 cup sour cream\n- 1/4 cup salsa\n\n## Instructions\n1. **Cook beef**: In a large skillet, cook ground beef over medium heat until browned. Drain excess fat. Stir in taco seasoning mix and water according to package instructions.\n2. **Prepare tortillas**: Warm tortillas in a dry skillet or microwave until soft.\n3. **Assemble tacos**: Fill each tortilla with ground beef, shredded lettuce, diced tomatoes, shredded cheese, sour cream, and salsa.\n4. **Serve**: Serve immediately with your favorite taco toppings.\n\n## Tips\n- Use ground turkey or chicken for a leaner option.\n- Add avocado or guacamole for extra creaminess.\n- Serve with lime wedges for a fresh burst of flavor.'),
(UNHEX('00112233445566778899AABBCCDDEE16'), 'Mac and Cheese', '2023-01-24', 5, 'Creamy and delicious mac and cheese.', 'Pasta', UNHEX('AABBCCDDEEFF00112233445566778899'), '# Mac and Cheese\n\n## Introduction\nCreamy and delicious mac and cheese that’s perfect for a comforting meal. This homemade version is easy to make and full of cheesy goodness.\n\n## Ingredients\n- 8 oz elbow macaroni\n- 2 tablespoons butter\n- 2 tablespoons all-purpose flour\n- 2 cups milk\n- 2 cups shredded cheddar cheese\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n\n## Instructions\n1. **Cook macaroni**: Cook macaroni according to package instructions. Drain and set aside.\n2. **Make roux**: In a large saucepan, melt butter over medium heat. Stir in flour and cook for 1-2 minutes until bubbly.\n3. **Add milk**: Gradually whisk in milk, and cook until thickened and bubbly.\n4. **Add cheese**: Stir in shredded cheese until melted and smooth. Season with salt and pepper.\n5. **Combine**: Add cooked macaroni to the cheese sauce and stir to combine.\n6. **Serve**: Serve hot, garnished with extra cheese if desired.\n\n## Tips\n- Use a mix of cheeses for extra flavor.\n- Add cooked bacon or ham for a heartier dish.\n- Bake with a breadcrumb topping for a crispy finish.'),
(UNHEX('00112233445566778899AABBCCDDEE17'), 'Crispy Baked Chicken Wings', '2023-01-25', 5, 'Crispy and flavorful baked chicken wings.', 'Appetizer', UNHEX('AABBCCDDEEFF00112233445566778899'), '# Crispy Baked Chicken Wings\n\n## Introduction\nCrispy and flavorful baked chicken wings that are perfect for game day or any gathering. These wings are easy to make and can be tossed in your favorite sauce.\n\n## Ingredients\n- 2 pounds chicken wings\n- 2 tablespoons vegetable oil\n- 1 teaspoon salt\n- 1/2 teaspoon black pepper\n- 1/2 teaspoon garlic powder\n- 1/2 teaspoon paprika\n- 1/4 teaspoon cayenne pepper\n\n## Instructions\n1. **Preheat oven**: Preheat your oven to 400°F (200°C). Line a baking sheet with parchment paper or foil.\n2. **Prepare wings**: In a large bowl, toss chicken wings with vegetable oil, salt, black pepper, garlic powder, paprika, and cayenne pepper until evenly coated.\n3. **Bake wings**: Arrange the wings in a single layer on the prepared baking sheet. Bake for 35-40 minutes, flipping halfway through, until crispy and golden brown.\n4. **Serve**: Serve hot with your favorite dipping sauce.\n\n## Tips\n- For extra crispy wings, bake on a wire rack set over the baking sheet.\n- Toss the wings in buffalo sauce, barbecue sauce, or honey garlic sauce after baking.\n- Serve with celery sticks and blue cheese dressing.');
